Here's a single self-contained HTML file you can save (e.g., sort-compare.html) and open in a browser. It animates three sorts side-by-side on the same initial random array: bubble sort, insertion sort, and quicksort (Lomuto partition). Each panel shows a bar chart, highlights comparisons and swaps, counts steps (comparisons + swaps), and displays a short explanation of time complexities.

