Below is a single-file, self-contained HTML page that does real-time email validation using a regular expression and shows green/red border feedback. The page also includes an explanation (visible in the page) of why regex-based validation is fundamentally limited by the RFCs, and practical alternatives you can use in production.

Copy this into a file (e.g., email-validator.html) and open it in a browser.

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8" />
  <title>Email validation demo (regex + explanation)</title>
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width,initial-scale=1" />
  <style>
    body { font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, "Segoe UI", Roboto, "Helvetica Neue", Arial; margin: 24px; color:#111; line-height:1.5;}
