Below is a single self-contained HTML file. It displays two side-by-side counter widgets:

- "Buggy counter" — intentionally contains a race condition: its handlers perform an asynchronous read/modify/write using setTimeout and share a single count variable, so rapid clicks cause overlapping updates that can read stale values and overwrite newer ones.
- "Fixed counter" — demonstrates a simple fix: updates are made serially by queuing operations so each increment is applied to the most recent value (here implemented by making each async task compute the new value from the previous task's promise/result, effectively serializing updates). Another common fix would be to use atomic update functions (update based on current value) or lock/mutex.

The page also includes visible explanation text describing why the race occurs and how the fix resolves it.

