Below is a single self-contained HTML file that implements a light/dark theme toggle using the Singleton pattern for theme state management. The singleton stores the current theme, exposes methods to toggle or set it, notifies registered listeners (so different UI components update), and persists the theme in localStorage. The page demonstrates the theme across varied elements (header, cards, buttons, form, table, code block, list, footer). At the end of the page there's a short discussion of singleton pros/cons and when dependency injection might be better.

