Notes on why the bug appears:
- JavaScript is single-threaded, but asynchronous callbacks can interleave. If you implement a read-modify-write across separate asynchronous steps, another callback may mutate the same variable between your read and write.
- The buggy demo intentionally increases the time between reading and writing to make races visible.
- The fix uses an aggregator that accepts contributions (deltas) so updates don't depend on a possibly stale read.

